Defendant Teonte D Adams in court with attorney Matt Last.  Defendant Teonte D Adams in custody.  Denis John Stingl for Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PSI reviewed by parties. State placed negotiations on the record. Court finds the state has complied with the victim rights legislation. Statements made as to sentencing.  

Exhibit 1 received.

As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 17 YEARS, with credit for 286 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 9 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 8 YEARS.  

Conditions:
1) Court set restitution at zero;
2) Pay all costs, fees, and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
3) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
4) Complete a psychological exam;
5) No weapons, firearms, bullets or armor;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal drugs & alcohol;
7) No contact with the victims, families, schools, co-actors or address of the offense;
8) Maintain fulltime employment or education and employment of at least 40 hours per week;
9) No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
10) No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription. Provide prescription to agent before filling it;
11) No contact with drug dealers, drug houses or places where drugs are sold, purchased, used, packaged, distributed or stored;
12) Complete Cognitive Thinking Program;
13) Complete Anger Management;
14) Complete GED or HSED;
15) Vocational programming;
16) Victim Impact panel.


Court costs, fees, and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/ wages.

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOTeligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

